#Text=# Implicit Neural Representation in Medical Imaging: A Comparative Survey
ICCV 2023 CVAMD Workshop
#Text=:fire::fire: This is a collection of awesome articles about Implicit Neural Representation networks in medical imaging:fire::fire:
#Text=:loudspeaker: Our review paper published on arXiv: [Implicit Neural Representation in Medical Imaging: A Comparative Survey](https://arxiv.org/abs/2307.16142) :heart:
#Text=  title={Implicit neural representation in medical imaging: A comparative survey},
#Text=  author={Molaei, Amirali and Aminimehr, Amirhossein and Tavakoli, Armin and Kazerouni, Amirhossein and Azad, Bobby and Azad, Reza and Merhof, Dorit},
#Text=  booktitle={Proceedings of the IEEE/CVF International Conference on Computer Vision},
#Text=Implicitly representing image signals has gained popularity in recent years for a broad range of medical imaging applications.
#Text=The most motivating reasons are the following:
#Text=* Memory efficiency: The amount of memory demanded to represent the signal is not restricted by the signal's resolution.
#Text=* Unlimited Resolution: They take values in the continuous domain, meaning they can generate values for coordinates in-between the pixel or voxel-wise grid
#Text=* Effective data usage: They can learn to handle reconstruction and synthesis tasks without high-cost external annotation.
#Text=Which all are significantly important for developing an automatic medical system.

#Text=With the aim of providing easier access for researchers, this repo contains a comprehensive paper list of Implicit Neural Representations in Medical Imaging, including papers, codes, and related websites.
#Text=We considered a sum of <u>**86**</u> research papers spanning from 2021 to 2023.
#Text=Here, we taxonomize studies that integrate implicit representations into building medical analysis models.
#Text=(Each section is ordered by the publication dates)
#Text=1. 📜 **IntraTomo: Self-supervised Learning-based Tomography via Sinogram Synthesis and Prediction**
#Text=   - 📖 Proceedings: IEEE/CVF International Conference on Computer Vision, 2021
#Text=   - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Guangming Zang, Ramzi Idoughi, Rui Li, Peter Wonka, Wolfgang Heidrich
#Text=   - 📌 Highlight: Uses coordinate-based neural representations for CT reconstructions, capturing details often overlooked by standard deep learning.
#Text=It's self-supervised, using the scanned object's own projections as training data, and further refined with geometric techniques.
#Text=2. 📜 **CoIL: Coordinate-based Internal Learning for Imaging Inverse Problems**
#Text=   - 📖 Journal: IEEE Transactions on Computational Imaging, 2021
#Text=   - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Yu Sun, Jiaming Liu, Mingyang Xie, Brendt Wohlberg, Ulugbek S.

#Text=   - 📌 Highlight: Takes measurement coordinates, such as view angle θ and spatial location l in CT scans, as its input, then outputs the corresponding sensor responses for these coordinates, creating an implicit neural representation of the measurement field.
#Text=3. 📜 **Dynamic CT Reconstruction from Limited Views with Implicit Neural Representations and Parametric Motion Fields**
#Text=   - 📖 Proceedings: IEEE/CVF International Conference on Computer Vision, 2021
#Text=Aditya Mohan, Kyle Champley, Jingu Kang, Suren Jayasuriya
#Text=   - 📌 Highlight: Uses implicit neural representations (INRs) for 4D-CT reconstruction.
#Text=Paired with a parametric motion field, they estimate evolving 3D objects.
#Text=Using a differentiable Radon transform, reconstructions are synthesized and compared with x-ray data, improving reconstruciton quality without training data.
#Text=   - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Kunal Gupta, Brendan Colvert, Francisco Contijoch
#Text=5. 📜 **Streak artifacts reduction algorithm using an implicit neural representation in sparse-view CT**
#Text=   - 📖 Conference: Medical Imaging 2022: Physics of Medical Imaging, 2022
#Text=   - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Byeongjoon Kim, Hyunjung Shim, Jongduk Baek
#Text=6. 📜 **Self-Supervised Coordinate Projection Network for Sparse-View Computed Tomography**
#Text=   - 📖 Journal: IEEE Transactions on Computational Imaging, 2023
#Text=   - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Qing Wu, Ruimin Feng, Hongjiang Wei, Jingyi Yu, Yuyao Zhang
#Text=7. 📜 **OReX: Object Reconstruction from Planar Cross-sections Using Neural Fields**
#Text=   - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Haim Sawdayee, Amir Vaxman, Amit H.
#Text=8. 📜 **NeuRec: Incorporating Interpatient prior to Sparse-View Image Reconstruction for Neurorehabilitation**
#Text=   - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Cong Liu, Qingbin Wang, Jing Zhang
#Text=9. 📜 **MEPNet: A Model-Driven Equivariant Proximal Network for Joint Sparse-View Reconstruction and Metal Artifact Reduction in CT Images.**
#Text=   - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Hong Wang, Minghao Zhou, Dong Wei, Yuexiang Li, Yefeng Zheng
#Text=10. 📜 **UncertaINR: Uncertainty Quantification of End-to-End Implicit Neural Representations for Computed Tomography**
#Text=    - 📖 Authors: Francisca Vasconcelos, Bobby He, Nalini Singh, Yee Whye Teh
#Text=11. 📜 **Unsupervised Polychromatic Neural Representation for CT Metal Artifact Reduction**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Qing Wu, Lixuan Chen, Ce Wang, Hongjiang Wei, S.
#Text=12. 📜 **NAISR: A 3D Neural Additive Model for Interpretable Shape Representation**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Yining Jiao, Carlton Zdanski, Julia Kimbell, Andrew Prince, Cameron Worden, Samuel Kirse, Christopher Rutter, Benjamin Shields, William Dunn
#Text=13. 📜 **An Arbitrary Scale Super-Resolution Approach for 3-Dimensional Magnetic Resonance Image using Implicit Neural Representation**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Qing Wu, Yuwei Li, Yawen Sun, Yan Zhou, Hongjiang Wei, Jingyi Yu, Yuyao Zhang
#Text=14. 📜 **IREM: High-Resolution Magnetic Resonance (MR) Image Reconstruction via Implicit Neural Representation**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Qing Wu, Yuwei Li, Lan Xu, Ruiming Feng, Hongjiang Wei, Qing Yang, Boliang Yu, Xiaozhao Liu, Jingyi Yu, Yuyao Zhang
#Text=15. 📜 **MRI Super-Resolution using Implicit Neural Representation with Frequency Domain Enhancement**
#Text=16. 📜 **NeSVoR: Implicit Neural Representation for Slice-to-Volume Reconstruction in MRI**
#Text=     - 🗓️ Publication Date: IEEE TRANSACTIONS ON MEDICAL IMAGING, 2022
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Junshen Xu, Daniel Moyer, Borjan Gagoski, Juan Eugenio Iglesias, P.
#Text=17. 📜 **Spatiotemporal implicit neural representation for unsupervised dynamic MRI reconstruction**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Jie Feng, Ruimin Feng, Qing Wu, Zhiyong Zhang, Yuyao Zhang, Hongjiang Wei
#Text=18. 📜 **Neural Implicit k-Space for Binning-free Non-Cartesian Cardiac MR Imaging**
#Text=      - 📖 Conference: International Conference on Information Processing in Medical Imaging, 2023
#Text=      - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Wenqi Huang, Hongwei Li, Jiazhen Pan, Gastao Cruz, Daniel Rueckert, Kerstin Hammernik
#Text=19. 📜 **Continuous longitudinal fetus brain atlas construction via implicit neural representation**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Lixuan Chen, Jiangjie Wu, Qing Wu, Hongjiang Wei, Yuyao Zhang
#Text=20. 📜 **Multi-contrast MRI Super-resolution via Implicit Neural Representations**
#Text=      - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Julian McGinnis, Suprosanna Shit, Hongwei Bran Li, Vasiliki Sideri-Lampretsa, Robert Graf, Maik Dannecker, Jiazhen Pan, Nil Stolt Ansö, Mark Mühlau, Jan S.
#Text=21. 📜 **Streak artifacts reduction algorithm using an implicit neural representation in sparse-view CT.**
#Text=      - 📖 Journal: *Medical Imaging 2022: Physics of Medical Imaging, 2022*
#Text=      - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Byeongjoon Kim, Hyunjung Shim, Jongduk Baek.*
#Text=22. 📜 **Spatial Attention-based Implicit Neural Representation for Arbitrary Reduction of MRI Slice Spacing**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Xin Wang, Sheng Wang, Honglin Xiong, Kai Xuan, Zixu Zhuang, Mengjun Liu, Zhenrong Shen, Xiangyu Zhao, Lichi Zhang, Qian Wang
#Text=23. 📜 **A scan-specific unsupervised method for parallel MRI reconstruction via implicit neural representation**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Ruimin Feng, Qing Wu, Yuyao Zhang, Hongjiang Wei
#Text=24. 📜 **Dual Arbitrary Scale Super-Resolution for Multi-Contrast MRI**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Jiamiao Zhang, Yichen Chi, Jun Lyu, Wenming Yang, Yapeng Tian
#Text=25. 📜 **Unsupervised reconstruction of accelerated cardiac cine MRI using Neural Fields**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Tabita Catalán, Matías Courdurier, Axel Osses, René Botnar, Francisco Sahli Costabal, Claudia Prieto
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: An unsupervised INR approach that uses the spatio-temporal Fourier Features of the heart's motion.
#Text=26. 📜 **Self-supervised arbitrary scale super-resolution framework for anisotropic MRI**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Haonan Zhang, Yuhan Zhang, Qing Wu, Jiangjie Wu, Zhiming Zhen, Feng Shi, Jianmin Yuan, Hongjiang Wei, Chen Liu, Yuyao Zhang
#Text=27. 📜 **Implicit Neural Networks with Fourier-Feature Inputs for Free-breathing Cardiac MRI Reconstruction**
#Text=28. 📜 **Implicit neural representations for unsupervised super-resolution and denoising of 4D flow MRI**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Simone Saitta, Marcello Carioni, Subhadip Mukherjee, Carola-Bibiane Schönlieb, Alberto Redaelli
#Text=29. 📜 **CoNeS: Conditional neural fields with shift modulation for multi-sequence MRI translation.**
#Text=      - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Yunjie Chen, Marius Staring, Olaf M.
#Text=30. 📜 **Batch Implicit Neural Representation for MRI Parallel Reconstruction.**
#Text=      - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Hao Li, Yusheng Zhou, Jianan Liu, Xiling Liu, Tao Huang, Zhihan Lv.*
#Text=      - 📌 Highlight: Uses INR to parametrize fully-sampled MRI images as continuous functions, enhanced by a scale-embedded encoder for scale-independent feature production.
#Text=31. 📜 **3D cine-magnetic resonance imaging using spatial and temporal implicit neural representation learning (STINR-MR).**
#Text=      - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Hua-Chieh Shao, Tielige Mengke, Jie Deng, and You Zhang.*

#Text=      - 📌 Highlight: The spatial implicit neural representation network maps 3D spatial coordinates to MR values, while the temporal implicit neural representation encodes time points to create dynamic motion fields
#Text=32. 📜 **NeRP: Implicit Neural Representation Learning with Prior Embedding for Sparsely Sampled Image Reconstruction**
#Text=    - 📖 Preprint: *IEEE Transactions on Neural Networks and Learning Systems, 2022*
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Liyue Shen, John Pauly, Lei Xing.*
#Text=33. 📜 **CuNeRF: Cube-Based Neural Radiance Field for Zero-Shot Medical Image Arbitrary-Scale Super Resolution**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Zixuan Chen, Jianhuang Lai, Lingxiao Yang, Xiaohua Xie
#Text=34. 📜 **ImplicitVol: Sensorless 3D Ultrasound Reconstruction with Deep Implicit Representation**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Pak-Hei Yeung, Linde Hesse, Moska Aliasi, Monique Haak, the INTERGROWTH-21st Consortium, Weidi Xie, Ana I.L.
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Ang Nan Gu, Purang Abolmaesumi, Christina Luong, Kwang Moo Yi*
#Text=36. 📜 **Going Off-Grid: Continuous Implicit Neural Representations for 3D Vascular Modeling**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Dieuwertje Alblas, Christoph Brune, Kak Khee Yeung, Jelmer M.
#Text=37. 📜 **Implicit Neural Representations for Breathing-compensated Volume Reconstruction in Robotic Ultrasound Aorta Screening**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Yordanka Velikova, Mohammad Farid Azampour, Walter Simson, Marco Esposito, Nassir Navab*
#Text=38. 📜 **Topology-Preserving Shape Reconstruction and Registration via Neural Diffeomorphic Flow.**
#Text=     - 📖 Conference: *Proceedings of the IEEE/CVF Conference on CVPR*
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Shanlin Sun, Kun Han, Deying Kong, Hao Tang, Xiangyi Yan, Xiaohui Xie.*
#Text=39. 📜 **Dynamic Cone-beam CT Reconstruction using Spatial and Temporal Implicit Neural Representation Learning (STINR).**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *You Zhang, Hua-Chieh Shao, Tinsu Pan, Tielige Mengke.*
#Text=40. 📜 **Learning Deep Intensity Field for Extremely Sparse-View CBCT Reconstruction.**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Yiqun Lin, Zhongjin Luo, Wei Zhao, Xiaomeng Li.*
#Text=41. 📜 **A Memory-Efficient Dynamic Image Reconstruction Method using Neural Fields.**

#Text=     - 📌 Highlight: The "Partition of Unity Network" (POUnet) is employed as a specialized neural field architecture to reconstruct dynamic biomedical images, which allows it to optimize against indirect and possibly noisy measurements, ensuring enhanced accuracy in dynamically evolving imaging scenarios.
#Text=42. 📜 **Going Off-Grid: Continuous Implicit Neural Representations for 3D Vascular Modeling**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Dieuwertje Alblas, Christoph Brune, Kak Khee Yeung, Jelmer M.
#Text=43. 📜 **Implicitatlas: learning deformable shape templates in medical imaging**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Jiancheng Yang, Udaranga Wickramasinghe, Bingbing Ni, Pascal Fua
#Text=44. 📜 **MiShape: 3D Shape Modelling of Mitochondria in Microscopy**
#Text=Punnakkal, Suyog S Jadhav, Alexander Horsch, Krishna Agarwal, Dilip K.
#Text=45. 📜 **Hybrid Neural Diffeomorphic Flow for Shape Representation and Generation via Triplane**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Kun Han, Shanlin Sun, Xiaohui Xie
#Text=46. 📜 **Hybrid-CSR: Coupling Explicit and Implicit Shape Representation for Cortical Surface Reconstruction**
#Text=     - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: Shanlin Sun, Thanh-Tung Le, Chenyu You, Hao Tang, Kun Han, Haoyu Ma, Deying Kong, Xiangyi Yan, Xiaohui Xie
#Text=47. 📜 **A self-supervised learning approach for high-resolution diffuse optical tomography using neural fields.**
#Text=SPIE 12753, Second Conference on Biomedical Photonics and Cross-Fusion (BPC 2023)
#Text=       - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Linlin Li, Siyuan Shen, Shengyu Gao, Yuehan Wang, Liangtao Gu, Shiying Li, Xingjun Zhu, Jiahua Jiang, Jingyi Yu, Wuwei Ren*
#Text=       - 📌 Highlight: A diffuse optical tomography (DOT) reconstructio approach where it translates spatial coordinates to the optical absorption coefficients they correspond to.
#Text=48. 📜 **INCODE: Implicit Neural Conditioning with Prior Knowledge Embeddings.**
#Text=       - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Amirhossein Kazerouni, Reza Azad, Alireza Hosseini, Dorit Merhof, Ulas Bagci*
#Text=49. 📜 **NeRD: Neural Representation of Distribution for Medical Image Segmentation**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Hang Zhang, Rongguang Wang, Jinwei Zhang, Chao Li, Gufeng Yang, Pascal Spincemaille, Thanh Nguyen, Yi Wang*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Addresses white matter lesion segmentation and left atrial segmentation.
#Text=50. 📜 **Implicit field learning for unsupervised anomaly detection in medical images**
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Aims to localize gliomas on brain MR images using an unsupervised out-of-distribution detection method.
#Text=51. 📜 **Direct localization and delineation of human pedunculopontine nucleus based on a self-supervised magnetic resonance image super-resolution method**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Jun Li, Xiaojun Guan, Qing Wu, Chenyu He, Weimin Zhang, Xiyue Lin, Chunlei Liu, Hongjiang Wei, Xiaojun Xu, Yuyao Zhang*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Focuses on delineating the pedunculopontine nucleus (PPN).
#Text=52. 📜 **Binary segmentation of medical images using implicit spline representations and deep learning**
#Text=Barrowclough, Georg Muntingh, Varatharajan Nainamalai, Ivar Stangeby*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Tackles image segmentation for a congenital heart disease computed tomography medical imaging dataset.
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Nil Stolt-Ansó, Julian McGinnis, Jiazhen Pan, Kerstin Hammernik, Daniel Rueckert*
#Text=54. 📜 **Retinal vessel segmentation based on self-distillation and implicit neural representation**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Jia Gu, Fangzheng Tian & Il-Seok Oh*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Concentrates on segmenting retinal blood vessels from retinal images.
#Text=55. 📜 **Deep Implicit Statistical Shape Models for 3D Medical Image Delineation**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Ashwin Raju, Shun Miao, Dakai Jin, Le Lu, Junzhou Huang, Adam P.
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Presents a methodology that emphasizes 3D delineation of anatomical structures using deep implicit statistical shape models.
#Text=56. 📜 **Implicit Neural Representations for Medical Imaging Segmentation**
#Text=    - 📖 Conference: *International Conference on Medical Image Computing and Computer-Assisted Intervention, 2022*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Specifically mentions 3D signals in medical imaging, hinting at 3D anatomical structures.
#Text=57. 📜 **Implicit Anatomical Rendering for Medical Image Segmentation with Stochastic Experts**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Chenyu You, Weicheng Dai, Yifei Min, Lawrence Staib, James S.
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Emphasizes refining the boundary regions of segmented medical images.
#Text=58. 📜 **I-MedSAM: Implicit Medical Image Segmentation with Segment Anything**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Xiaobao Wei, Jiajun Cao, Yizhu Jin, Ming Lu, Guangyu Wang, Shanghang Zhang*
#Text=59. 📜 **SwIPE: Efficient and Robust Medical Image Segmentation with Implicit Patch Embeddings**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Yejia Zhang, Pengfei Gu, Nishchal Sapkota, Danny Z.
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Uses implicit neural representations to predict shapes at the patch level, balancing both local boundary delineation and global shape coherence.
#Text=60. 📜 **Implicit Neural Representations for Deformable Image Registration**
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Implicit deformable image registration using a neural network to represent continuous transformations
#Text=61. 📜 **Learning Homeomorphic Image Registration via Conformal-Invariant Hyperelastic Regularisation**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Jing Zou, Noémie Debroux, Lihao Liu, Jing Qin, Carola-Bibiane Schönlieb, Angelica I Aviles-Rivero*
#Text=It discusses a novel regularizer based on conformal-invariant properties.
#Text=62. 📜 **Deformable Image Registration with Geometry-informed Implicit Neural Representations**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Louis van Harten, Rudolf Leonardus Mirjam Van Herten, Jaap Stoker, Ivana Isgum*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Parameterizes the deformation field by incorporating the geometry encoding of anatomical structures to guide the deformation process.
#Text=63. 📜 **Implicit neural representations for joint decomposition and registration of gene expression images in the marmoset brain.**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Michal Byra, Charissa Poon, Tomomi Shimogori, Henrik Skibbe*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Addresses the registration of brain images with added features or artifacts by emphasizing the decomposition of images into support and residual components.
#Text=64. 📜 **INR-LDDMM: Fluid-based Medical Image Registration Integrating Implicit Neural Representation and Large Deformation Diffeomorphic Metric Mapping.**
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Combines implicit neural representation with Large Deformable Diffeomorphic Metric Mapping (LDDMM) in a coarse-to-fine approach.
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Shanlin Sun, Kun Han, Hao Tang, Deying Kong, Junayed Naushad, Xiangyi Yan, Xiaohui Xie*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Introduces a distinction between general deformable registration and diffeomorphic image registration using neural fields.
#Text=66. 📜 **Diffeomorphic Image Registration with Neural Velocity Field**
#Text=    - 📖 Conference: *IEEE/CVF Winter Conference on Applications of Computer Vision, 2023*
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Kun Han, Shanlin Sun, Xiangyi Yan, Chenyu You, Hao Tang, Junayed Naushad, Haoyu Ma, Deying Kong, Xiaohui Xie*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Introduces a cascaded framework for diffeomorphic Image Registration with Neural Velocity Field (DNVF) by modeling the space of transformations.
#Text=67. 📜 **NePhi: Neural Deformation Fields for Approximately Diffeomorphic Medical Image Registration**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Lin Tian, Soumyadip Sengupta, Hastings Greer, Raúl San José Estépar, Marc Niethammer*
#Text=68. 📜 **Exploring the performance of implicit neural representations for brain image registration**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Michal Byra, Charissa Poon, Muhammad Febrian Rachmadi, Matthias Schlachter, Henrik Skibbe*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Investigated the effectiveness of INRs in enhancing brain image registration within MRI settings
#Text=69. 📜 **Dynamic Neural Fields for Learning Atlases of 4D Fetal MRI Time-series**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Zeen Chi, Zhongxiao Cong, Clinton J.
#Text=Wang, Yingcheng Liu, Esra Abaci Turk, P.
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: The method is primarily focused on registration to enable motion stabilization, but it also uses a form of reconstruction to build the atlas itself from the registered data.
#Text=
#Text=### Reconstruction from Limited or Sparse Views
#Text=70. 📜 **MedNeRF: Medical Neural Radiance Fields for Reconstructing 3D-aware CT-Projections from a Single X-ray.**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Abril Corona-Figueroa, Jonathan Frawley, Sam Bond-Taylor, Sarath Bethapudi, Hubert P.
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Reconstruct CT projections from a few or a single-view X-ray, based on neural radiance fields.
#Text=The proposed technique minimizes patients' exposure to ionizing radiation.
#Text=71. 📜  **NAF: Neural Attenuation Fields for Sparse-View CBCT Reconstruction.**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Ruyi Zha, Yanhao Zhang, Hongdong Li.*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: A self-supervised approach for CBCT reconstruction that requires no external training data, using a deep neural network to represent attenuation coefficients.
#Text=72. 📜 **SNAF: Sparse-view CBCT Reconstruction with Neural Attenuation Fields.**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Yu Fang, Lanzhuju Mei, Changjian Li, Yuan Liu, Wenping Wang, Zhiming Cui, Dinggang Shen.*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Can reconstruct high-quality CBCT images from limited 2D projections, addressing concerns about radiation dose and image quality in dental applications.
#Text=73. 📜 **3D reconstructions of brain from MRI scans using neural radiance fields.**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Khadija Iddrisu, Sylwia Malec, Alessandro Crimi.*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Uses neural radiance fields to reconstruct 3D MRI images from 2D MRI slices, aiming to reduce scan acquisition times and potential motion artifacts.
#Text=74. 📜 **TiAVox: Time-aware Attenuation Voxels for Sparse-view 4D DSA Reconstruction.**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Zhenghong Zhou, Huangxuan Zhao, Jiemin Fang, Dongqiao Xiang, Lei Chen, Lingxia Wu, Feihong Wu, Wenyu Liu, Chuansheng Zheng, Xinggang Wang.*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: A method for high-quality sparse-view 4D DSA reconstruction, reducing the required radiation dose and increasing the efficiency of 4D imaging in diagnosing vascular diseases.
#Text=75. 📜 **Neural Rendering for Stereo 3D Reconstruction of Deformable Tissues in Robotic Surgery.**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Yuehao Wang, Yonghao Long, Siu Hin Fan, Qi Dou.*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Uses dynamic neural radiance fields to reconstruct deformable tissues during robotic surgery from stereo video captures
#Text=76. 📜 **EndoSurf: Neural Surface Reconstruction of Deformable Tissues with Stereo Endoscope Videos.**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Ruyi Zha, Xuelian Cheng, Hongdong Li, Mehrtash Harandi, Zongyuan Ge.*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Learns and represents a deforming surface from RGBD sequences captured via endoscope, offering improvements in high-fidelity shape reconstructions.
#Text=77. 📜 **Ultra-NeRF: Neural Radiance Fields for Ultrasound Imaging.**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Magdalena Wysocki, Mohammad Farid Azampour, Christine Eilers, Benjamin Busam, Mehrdad Salehi, Nassir Navab.*

#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Introduces a physics-enhanced implicit neural representation for ultrasound imaging which accounts for view-dependent changes in appearance and geometry, improving the quality of synthesized ultrasound images.
#Text=78. 📜 **Oral-NeXF: 3D Oral Reconstruction with Neural X-ray Field from Panoramic Imaging.**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Weinan Song, Haoxin Zheng, Jiawei Yang, Chengwen Liang, Lei He.*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Proposes a solution for 3D reconstruction of oral structures using a single panoramic X-ray, with a model that learns to represent the 3D oral structure implicitly
#Text=79. 📜 **Robust Single-view Cone-beam X-ray Pose Estimation with Neural Tuned Tomography (NeTT) and Masked Neural Radiance Fields (mNeRF).**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Chaochao Zhou, Syed Hasib Akhter Faruqui, Abhinav Patel, Ramez N.
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: A method for pose estimation of radiolucent objects via X-ray projections.
#Text=Two high-fidelity view synthesis methods (NeTT and mNeRF) are introduced, with NeTT being highlighted for its computational efficiency and generalization capabilities.
#Text=
#Text=80. 📜 **SCI: A Spectrum Concentrated Implicit Neural Compression for Biomedical Data.**
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Runzhao Yang, Tingxiong Xiao, Yuxiao Cheng, Qianni Cao, Jinyuan Qu, Jinli Suo, Qionghai Dai.*

#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Introduces an adaptive partitioning strategy to divide data into spectrum-concentrated blocks, a funnel-shaped INR structure for efficient data compression, and an allocation strategy for INR parameters.
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Runzhao Yang, Tingxiong Xiao, Yuxiao Cheng, Jinli Suo, Qionghai Dai.*

#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Uses ensemble learning and a divide-and-conquer approach to compress different regions and organizes the data using a tree structure to extract shared parameters, removing redundancy and ensuring continuity.
#Text=    - 🧑‍🔬 Authors: *Emilien Dupont, Hrushikesh Loya, Milad Alizadeh, Adam Goliński, Yee Whye Teh, Arnaud Doucet.*
#Text=    - 📌 Highlight: Uses meta-learning to reduce encoding time and introduces shared structures and modulation for compression across different modalities.
#Text=83. 📜 **A Novel Implicit Neural Representation for Volume Data**
#Text=     - 📌 Highlight: Introduces a new implicit neural representation to compress high-resolution medical volume data and shows high speed and quality in compression compared to existing works.
